At least 18 people died and dozens were feared trapped in rubble after a strong earthquake struck off Aceh province on Indonesia&#8217;s Sumatra island on Wednesday, officials said.&#8220;Eighteen have died so far, based on data from the hospital. Some of the fatalities are children,&#8221; Said Mulyadi, deputy district chief of Pidie Jaya, the region hit hardest by the quake, told AFP.-AFP